description:
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Admin Team Leader in General Surgery &amp; Urology, Coastal Integrated Service Unit&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit &lt;strong&gt;two&lt;/strong&gt; enthusiastic, highly motivated and experienced Admin Team Leaders for the General Surgery &amp; Urology team. The right person(s) will be forward thinking, wanting to embrace and suggest change with a clear direction on engaging team working in a busy environment. The ability to multi task and work to deadlines is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will be on a permanent contract working Monday to Friday (37.5 hours).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;The ideal candidate must have:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a good standard of education to include GCSE in Maths and English (Grade A to C);&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have proven keyboard skills and a minimum of a NVQ level 3 or equivalent in Administration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in providing leadership and change management is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;You will need to:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;be a team player with customer care experience, experience of working within a hospital environment and using databases such as PAS, Infoflex and Microsoft applications; and&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;have a good understanding of RTT pathways as well as awareness and understanding of other national targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have full line management responsibility for the General Surgery &amp; Urology team including recruitment, local induction, informal conduct and sickness/annual leave. They will also have responsibility for workload management and delegation across the team. Your responsibilities will also include timetabling for clinical teams and coordinating their leave.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the ability to work both independently and as part of a wider team with excellent written and verbal communication skills and organisational abilities. The Trust is an ever-changing environment and you would need to be able to retain your focus on providing an excellent service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Mandy Wellsted, Practice Manager on 01803 656253 or email: amanda.wellsted@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is Permanent contract working 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
